<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Installing the Required Packages</div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt; sudp apt-get update</div><div>=&gt; sudo apt-get install adb</div><div>=&gt; sudo apt-get install abootimg</div><div>=&gt; sudo apt-get install fastboot</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;">Accessing the Android Device</span></div><div># I am using the VM Ubuntu 16.04 on the VBox</div><div># The USB Port need to accept the connection from the device.</div><div># So, after connecting the device go to the “Settings” -&gt; “Ports” -&gt; “USB”</div><div># and add (+) . You should be able to choose the “Android [xxxx]”.</div><div><br /></div><div># Disconnect and reconnect the device</div><div>=&gt; adb devices</div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">List of devices attached</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">e72fb810    no permissions</span></div><div><br /></div><div> # Use Ubuntu only to unpack, modify and pack files after you have</div><div># copied to a local folder.</div><div>#  It won’t have the root privileges to talk to the device.</div><div>#  Things like install/remove, backup and dealing with the file systems</div><div># use the MAC OS X Terminal.</div><div> </div></en-note>